The Nim binary dynamically links against glibc and SDL2. If you really want to statically link against a C standard library, musl works just fine:<p><pre><code>    @if musl:
      passL = &quot;-static&quot;
      gcc.exe = &quot;/usr/local/musl/bin/musl-gcc&quot;
      gcc.linkerexe = &quot;/usr/local/musl/bin/musl-gcc&quot;
    @end
</code></pre>
Now it compiles like this (SDL2 is still dynamically loaded, +1 MB for that):<p><pre><code>    $ nim -d:release -d:musl c src/nimes
    $ ls -lha src/nimes
    -rwxr-xr-x 1 def users 219K Mai  1 22:00 src/nimes*</code></pre>
